                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-848" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-848" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-848" type="surname" value="CORBETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-848" type="given" value="FRANCES"></interp>FRANCES CORBETT</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with Edward Harris, tobacconist, in Ray-street, At a quarter past six o'clock, in the evening of the 24th of July, I was sit<lb></lb>ting within the inner door of the shop—I saw the prisoner standing with his hand on the counter, in the front shop—I had just before dusted the counter, and put the weights together—I asked what he wanted, and he asked if we sold brass tobacco-boxes—I said, "No"—he went away—I looked on the counter, and the weights were gone—I pursued, and stopped him on Clerkes<lb></lb>well-green—I saw a little boy pick up the 1/4 lb. weight, and give it to my bro<lb></lb>ther on Clerkenwell-green—these are the weights—I bought them myself, and know them well.</p>
